    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">Apparently sent to Washington via military channels,
                        and forwarded by the White House Map Room to <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> at Hyde Park.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-31">31 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President. Number 482. Most secret and personal.</p>
                <p>My immediately preceding telegram, para 1: Your humble servant, yourself and the
                        <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss> respectively.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
